.TH "make_rc_ack" 9 "make_rc_ack" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
make_rc_ack \- construct a response packet (ACK, NAK, or RDMA read)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" make_rc_ack
.BI "(struct hfi1_ibdev *dev "  ","
.BI "struct rvt_qp *qp "  ","
.BI "struct ib_other_headers *ohdr "  ","
.BI "struct hfi1_pkt_state *ps "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
the device for this QP
.IP "qp" 12
a pointer to the QP
.IP "ohdr" 12
a pointer to the IB header being constructed
.IP "ps" 12
the xmit packet state
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Return 1 if constructed; otherwise, return 0.
Note that we are in the responder's side of the QP context.
Note the QP s_lock must be held.
